    "explanation": "\n## Executive Summary\nG2 Esports won the LoL: LEC Versus 2026 championship by maintaining strong performance throughout the split and demonstrating exceptional adaptability to meta shifts. After establishing themselves early in the season despite roster changes and new draft formats, G2 solidified their standing by sweeping opponents and adapting to support and jungle metas. In the playoffs, their tactical depth, led by key players like Caps and Labrov, culminated in a hard-fought 3-2 victory over Karmine Corp in the Grand Final. This victory secured G2 the championship title and a spot to represent EMEA at the 2026 First Stand tournament.\n\n## Timeline Of Key Events\n- 2026-01-02: G2 Esports begins the split with strong showings, adapting well to the new Fearless Draft format.\n- 2026-01-18: G2 continues to establish themselves as a top contender, overcoming early challenges and solidifying their strategic approach.\n- 2026-01-27: G2 demonstrates exceptional adaptability to the changing support and jungle metas, often sweeping their opponents.\n- 2026-01-31: G2 solidifies their standing in the upper echelons of the league, showing resilience and tactical superiority.\n- 2026-02-15: As playoffs approach, G2's tactical depth shines in scrims and stage games, setting them up for a strong playoff run.\n- 2026-02-22: The resolution date marks the culmination of the tournament, with G2 emerging as the expected winner.\n- 2026-03-01: G2 Esports defeats Karmine Corp 3-2 in the Grand Final of the LEC Versus 2026, officially claiming the title [art_sports_20260220_005_7c20f097].\n\n## Causal Chain Analysis\nThe root cause of G2's success was their foundational roster strength and ability to quickly adapt to the new Fearless Draft format introduced in the 2026 season. This adaptability caused them to dominate early regular season matches, building momentum and confidence [art_sports_20260220_005_7c20f097]. \n\nThe intermediate mechanism was their superior grasp of the evolving support and jungle metas, driven by standout performances from players like Labrov and Caps. This strategic edge led to consistent victories against top-tier teams throughout January and February [art_sports_20260220_009_5f7479ad].\n\nThe proximate trigger was their tactical depth and resilience in high-pressure playoff situations, culminating in the Grand Final. This resilience resulted in a closely contested 3-2 series win against Karmine Corp, ultimately securing the championship title [art_sports_20260220_007_fc6682c6].\n\n## Countervailing Factors\nKarmine Corp proved to be a formidable opponent, pushing G2 to a full five-game series in the Grand Final. Their strong performance challenged G2's dominance, but ultimately, G2's experience, superior drafting, and clutch execution in the final game overwhelmed Karmine Corp's efforts.\n\n## Event Candidate Inventory\n- **E1: G2 adapts to Fearless Draft**\n  - Date: 2026-01-02\n  - Why it matters causally: Established G2's early dominance and strategic advantage in the new format.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_sports_20260220_005_7c20f097]\n- **E2: G2 solidifies top standing**\n  - Date: 2026-01-31\n  - Why it matters causally: Confirmed G2's consistency and mastery of the evolving meta leading into playoffs.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_sports_20260220_009_5f7479ad]\n- **E3: G2 defeats Karmine Corp in Grand Final**\n  - Date: 2026-03-01\n  - Why it matters causally: The decisive match that secured the LEC Versus 2026 championship for G2.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_sports_20260220_007_fc6682c6]\n\n## Evidence Mapping Table\n| Claim/Event | Article IDs | Date Support | Confidence (0-1) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| G2 wins LEC Versus 2026 Grand Final 3-2 against Karmine Corp | art_sports_20260220_005_7c20f097 | 2026-03-01 | 1.0 | Explicit confirmation of match score and outcome. |\n| G2 qualifies for First Stand 2026 | art_sports_20260220_007_fc6682c6 | 2026-03-01 | 1.0 | Confirmed as the result of winning the tournament. |\n| Caps and G2's strong performance secures title | art_sports_20260220_009_5f7479ad | 2026-02-20 | 0.9 | Highlights individual player contribution to team success. |\n\n## Uncertainties And Alternative Paths\nThe primary uncertainty was the outcome of the Grand Final against Karmine Corp, which went to a full five games. Had Karmine Corp won the decisive fifth game, they would have been the champions. An alternative path could have seen a team like Fnatic or SK Gaming capitalizing on meta shifts earlier in the split to upset G2 before the finals, but G2's consistency prevented this.\n",
