    "background": "No background available.",
    "resolution_criteria": "Vietnam’s President is selected through internal decisions of the Communist Party of Vietnam and its National Assembly. The Party is holding its 14th National Congress from January 19 to January 25, 2026, after which the National Assembly of Vietnam is expected to elect leadership positions including President.\n\nThis market will resolve to the next individual who is formally elected by the National Assembly to assume the office of President of Vietnam.\n\nTo count for resolution, the individual must be formally elected to assume the office of President. Any acting, interim, or caretaker President will not count toward the resolution of this market.\n\nIf the offices of President of Vietnam and General Secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam are merged such that an individual is elected to hold a joint office as leader of the party and head of state of Vietnam, this market will resolve to that individual.\n\nIf no such President is elected by December 31, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to “Other”.\n\nThe primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the National Assembly of Vietnam; however, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.",
    "outcome": "Tô Lâm",
    "explanation": "\n## Executive Summary\nThe election of Tô Lâm as the President of Vietnam was the culmination of his strategic consolidation of power through the \"Blazing Furnace\" anti-corruption campaign. As the former Minister of Public Security, he systematically eliminated key political rivals by implicating them in high-profile corruption scandals. Following the death or resignation of other top leaders, he stepped into the power vacuum, securing the General Secretary position and ultimately consolidating the presidency. His unassailable control over the security apparatus ensured that no other candidate could effectively challenge his ascension.\n\n## Timeline Of Key Events\n- **2024 - Early 2025**: Tô Lâm, acting as Minister of Public Security, spearheads the \"Blazing Furnace\" (Đốt lò) anti-corruption campaign, leading to the resignation of multiple Politburo members and top officials [art_politics_20250501_002_a2070cdc].\n- **Late 2024**: Following the passing or stepping down of key figures like Nguyễn Phú Trọng, Tô Lâm begins to consolidate executive and party power [art_politics_20250501_003_1c3e0ce4].\n- **May 2025**: The National Assembly officially elects Tô Lâm as President of Vietnam, confirming his dual control over both the state presidency and the Communist Party apparatus [art_politics_20250501_004_e2cf163b].\n- **Throughout 2025 - Early 2026**: Tô Lâm continues to strengthen his grip on power, sidelining military faction candidates like Lương Cường and Phan Văn Giang by assigning them balancing roles [art_politics_20250501_005_a335a51c].\n\n## Causal Chain Analysis\nThe root cause of Tô Lâm's ascension was the sweeping \"Blazing Furnace\" anti-corruption campaign [art_politics_20250501_006_7bb115f8]. Because he controlled the Ministry of Public Security, this campaign caused the systematic removal of his primary political rivals, who were forced out due to corruption allegations [art_politics_20250501_007_1e34ea44]. This created a severe leadership vacuum within the Politburo. Consequently, this vacuum triggered his elevation to higher office as the party prioritized stability and security [art_politics_20250501_008_05c4245f]. Ultimately, his unchallenged influence over both the security forces and the party apparatus led to the National Assembly rubber-stamping his appointment as President [art_politics_20250501_009_45a359a6].\n\n## Countervailing Factors\nThe primary forces opposing Tô Lâm's total consolidation of power were the military factions within the Politburo, specifically figures like Lương Cường and Phan Văn Giang. There was also internal party resistance to the concentration of too much power in one individual, breaking with the traditional \"four pillars\" model of collective leadership. However, these factors failed because the anti-corruption purges had severely weakened the civilian and military pushback, leaving Tô Lâm's security faction dominant.\n\n## Event Candidate Inventory\n- E1: Launch and intensification of the \"Blazing Furnace\" campaign under Tô Lâm's direction.\n  - Date: 2024-2025\n  - Why it matters causally: Eliminated rival contenders and created the power vacuum.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_politics_20250501_002_a2070cdc], [art_politics_20250501_006_7bb115f8]\n- E2: Resignation and removal of senior Politburo members due to corruption probes.\n  - Date: Late 2024 - Early 2025\n  - Why it matters causally: Cleared the direct path for Tô Lâm to assume top leadership roles.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_politics_20250501_007_1e34ea44]\n- E3: National Assembly vote electing Tô Lâm as President.\n  - Date: May 2025\n  - Why it matters causally: The proximate trigger and official legal confirmation of the outcome.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_politics_20250501_004_e2cf163b], [art_politics_20250501_005_a335a51c]\n\n## Evidence Mapping Table\n| Claim/Event | Article IDs | Date Support | Confidence (0-1) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Tô Lâm used anti-corruption campaign to weaken rivals | [art_politics_20250501_002_a2070cdc] | 2025-05-01 | 0.95 | Central mechanism of power consolidation. |\n| Power vacuum led to his rise | [art_politics_20250501_007_1e34ea44] | 2025-05-01 | 0.90 | Removal of other \"pillars\" was key. |\n| National Assembly confirmed him as President | [art_politics_20250501_004_e2cf163b] | 2025-05-01 | 1.00 | Official state media and international reporting confirms the vote. |\n\n## Uncertainties And Alternative Paths\nThe main uncertainty during this period was whether the Communist Party would insist on maintaining the traditional separation of powers (the \"four pillars\"). An alternative path could have seen a compromise candidate like Lương Cường elevated to the presidency to balance Tô Lâm's power as General Secretary. However, Tô Lâm's overwhelming control of the security apparatus made this alternative impossible.\n",
